>In 1972-75 I was involved in the operation of a farm in Pine Grove, Pa. We
>were raising goats and ducks and chickens, and a truck garden and growing
>grains in the surrounding fields. 
>
>Sometime during that era during the summer months we were being visited by
>a large silent silvery craft that was shaped like a teardrop when viewed
>from the bottom with a large red light right in the middle surrounded by
>many other light emmitting types of "organs" seemingly to be everywhere all
>over the craft.
>
>This vessel would appear every Saturday night at midnight like clock-work.
>We could first tell it was coming becouse we could "feel" its immanent
>arrival. At first we didn't know what was about to occur. After the first
>few visits it became uncanny; as the behavior of the animals altered;
>uneasy and restless activity, and a general unsettled feeling as if
>something impending was about to occur.
>
>Lights streaming through the trees on a knoll near the farmhouse was the
>first sign of our "visitors". Then the craft would slowly ascend over the
>tree tops and appoach our "group" awaiting the visitors. The vessel would
>then with a wobble hover over us at about 50 ft then the centrally located
>red light would come on and go off, come on and go off. Slowly at first
>then more quickly until it was a steady light with all of us standing in
>it.
>At the same time the light would go on we could feel a resonance fill our
>bodies from head to foot. but this feeling would stop immediatly when the
>light would terminate or go off.
